2) English

a) History of the idea.

One day (quite recently), it turned out that I write / I need a piece of code that would have the task of sending and downloading files from ftp. I thought may Qt?
I played quite a long QFtp, but despite all my attempts did not work. Ba did not even want to connect to the server. A code was taken straight from the example of sitting in the man.
Well, well. I was looking on and so on that I found on libcurl. First, read a cornet, then what interested me the manual and example. However, despite this reading in the original version as
and the translator translated. Yes, I know translator. A lot do not understand ... Not discouraged, I decided to take the example of simple rule of thumb the libcurl and adjust to each other.
That would be quite easy to use. After a few problems (linking, etc.) I was able to compile the first example for downloading files from the server. So I took to be sending.
Here already were larger and had no problems forum (address given at the end), you probably still męczyłbym above compilation. There was little need popoprawiać code example.
I took everything together, I gave the appropriate functions. I decided to put it on the Gita. Why? Looking through the internet (Polish web page) I noticed that a lot of people are tired,
to use libcurl in your program.

b) Assumptions (Objectives):

-Creating nicely described the class / function that would be occupied only downloading / sending a file to / from ftp via libcurl.
-Transmitted by the arguments was the source path and target. So many think would be enough. Well, maybe even the name under which the record.
-Describe what and how it works.
-I would be as much code in C + + to simplify everything (if possible)

